President Obama has announced the appointment of Ambassador Jeffrey Davidow as the White House Advisor for the Summit of the Americas. The summit will be held in Trinidad and Tobago on April 17-19, and President Obama is looking forward to discussions with the leaders at the summit. Ambassador Davidow, who has taken a leave of absence from his position as President of the Institute of the Americas at the University of California at San Diego, will oversee preparations for the President's participation in the summit and help manage Summit-related diplomacy in the region. Ambassador Davidow has had a long career in the Foreign Service, serving in various positions in Latin America and Africa before retiring in 2003.